<div id="review_16153903" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/16153903" />
    <a title="Emily" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/871545-emily"><img alt="Emily" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1238526366p2/871545.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/16153903?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emily" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emily" href="/user/show/871545-emily">Emily</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer16153903" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10694743450565978908"> A must-read for any Lewis fan. He began the book as an unbeliever (a case against God) and finished it some 30 years later fully converted. Almost autobiographical, you get a real sense of his own spiritual awakening. It is claimed to be his personal favorite. The name comes from the scripture: &quot;Now we see through a glass, darkly: but then face to face..shall I know even as also I am known.&quot; <br/><br/>Better than anything I&apos;ve read, it describes the process of developing faith and finding and becoming li</span>
  <span id="freeText10694743450565978908" style="display:none"> A must-read for any Lewis fan. He began the book as an unbeliever (a case against God) and finished it some 30 years later fully converted. Almost autobiographical, you get a real sense of his own spiritual awakening. It is claimed to be his personal favorite. The name comes from the scripture: "Now we see through a glass, darkly: but then face to face..shall I know even as also I am known." <br /><br />Better than anything I've read, it describes the process of developing faith and finding and becoming like God. Amazing! <br /><br />The actual Cupid &amp; Psyche myth is summarized in the back of the book. Read it first for context.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10694743450565978908" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


